#: Game.Levels.InnerProductWorld.Level01
msgid "`norm_v` is how we define vector norms. It can also be written as `‖v‖`. We define the norm of a vector\n"
"`v` as the square root of it's inner product with itself. The lean code defining this is\n"
"\n"
"```\n"
"def norm_v (v : V) : ℝ := Real.sqrt ⟪v, v⟫.re\n"
"```"
